<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-07-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-07-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="167" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d167">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName>
                                to Prime Minister <persName type="to">Churchill</persName>
                            </hi><note n="1" xml:id="d167fn1">Sent to the United States Naval
                                Attaché, London, via Navy channels.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                <lb/>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-07-14">July 14, 1943</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Personal and secret for <gloss target="#t_FNP1">Former Naval
                                Person</gloss> from the President. Number 314.</p>
                        <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                        <p>I have no further word from <gloss target="#t_UJ1">U.J.</gloss> Even if
                            he is unable to get away, I think the time would be ripe for a Staff
                            Conference of all of us in General Wolfe’s stronghold around the first
                            of September.</p>
                        <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>